==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[munt]]''

====Noun====
'''mount'''

# A [[mountain]], as in ''Mount Everest''
# A horse
#: ''The rider climbed onto his '''mount'''.''
# The number of riders in a [[cavalry]] unit or division
#: ''The General said he has 2,000 '''mounts'''.''

